IRS990.Desc: RESOURCE PROGRAM - STAFF MONITOR GOVERNMENTAL, INDUSTRIAL, MILITARY, AND OTHER OPERATIONS AFFECTING NATURAL RESOURCES. MAINTAIN A FULL-TIME LEGISLATIVE SERVICE PROVIDING INFORMATION RELATING TO CONSERVATION AND ENVIROMENTAL MATTERS TO THE MICHIGAN LEGISLATURE, GOVERNOR'S OFFICE AND STATE OF MICHIGAN AND FEDERAL AGENCIES. INFORMS MEMBERS AND THE PUBLIC REGARDING DEVELOPMENTS AND ISSUES ON THE CONSERVATION FRONT. ENGAGES IN ENVIRONMENTAL LITIGATION TO PROTECT MICHIGAN'S NATURAL RESOURCES. SERVES AS THE OFFICIAL MICHIGAN AFFILIATE OF THE NATIONAL WILDLIFE FOUNDATION.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: MICHIGAN OUT-OF-DOORS PUBLICATION - THIS IS A PUBLICATION SUPPLIED TO APPROXIMATELY 9,500 MEMBERS IN PRINT 12,500 DIGITALLY (QUARTLERLY AVERAGE) AND WHICH IS DEVOTED TO CONSERVATION AND OUTDOOR RECREATION.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: ONE-WEEK THEMED OUTDOOR ACTIVITIES ENGAGING YOUTH IN DAY CAMP EXPERIENCES. EDUCATION OPPORTUNITIES FOCUS ON ENVIRONMENTAL CONSERVATION, ECOLOGY, WILDLIFE AND OUTDOOR ACTIVITIES. 137 YOUTH REGISTERED DURING THE ONE WEEK OF PROGRAM OPERATION IN 2022.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: MICHIGAN UNITED CONSERVATION CLUBS HAS MEMBERS THAT MAY ELECT MEMBERS OF THE GOVERNING BODY. THE CLASSIFICATION OF SUCH MEMBERS INCLUDE MEMBER CLUBS, JUNIOR MEMBER CLUBS, STATEWIDE CUBS, SUSTAINING MEMBERS, INDIVIDUAL MEMBERS, AND LIFE MEMBERS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE 990 IS RECEIVED BY THE ORGANIZATION'S EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR AND CFO, WHO REVIEW THE RETURN FOR ACCURACY. AFTER APPROVAL BY THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR, THE 990 IS MADE AVAILABLE TO THE FINANCE COMMITTEE. AFTER ANY CONCERNS PRESENTED BY THE FINANCE COMMITTEE ARE ADDRESSED, THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR SIGNS AND FILES THE RETURN.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ALL BOARD OF DIRECTORS ARE REQUIRED TO DISCLOSE ANY CONFLICTS OF INTERESTAND TO NOTIFY THE BOARD OF ANY CONFLICTS THAT MAY ARISE THROUGHOUT THE YEAR.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE, COMPRISED OF INDEPENDENT PERSONS, MEETS TO REVIEW THE PERFORMANCE OF THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR ANNUALLY. THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEERE VIEWS COMPARISON DATA FROM SIMILAR ORGANIZATIONS AS REPORTED BY AVAILABLE PUBLIC DOCUMENTS. A RECORD OF THE MEETING AND DECISION BY THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE IS RETAINED BY THE ORGANIZATION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ALL INFORMATION IS AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST. FORM 990 IS ALSO POSTED ANNUALLY ON GUIDESTAR'S WEBSITE. MICHIGAN UNITED CONSERVATION CLUBS IS LICENSED TO SOLICIT IN THAT STATE OF MICHIGAN AND PROVIDES FORM 990 AND AUDITED FINANCIAL STAEMENTS TO THE MICHIGAN ATTORNEY GENERAL'S OFFICE WHERE IT IS PUBLIC INFORMATION.
THE PROCESS HAS NOT CHANGED SINCE THE PRIOR YEAR.
